title: Vegan Passport
description:
Travel the world with confidence and enjoy local dishes without compromising your vegan beliefs! With your trusty Vegan guide, you can be sure of finding vegan food in restaurants around the globe.
This multilingual vegan guide is a must-have for globetrotting vegans. Itâ€™s small enough to slip into your pocket, but big enough to include the languages of over 96% of the worldâ€™s population.
The fifth edition of this essential guide has been updated and expanded, and now boasts 78 languages including Hausa, Igbo, Xhosa and Zulu.
Including fail-safe pictures, which can be used when words donâ€™t work, the Vegan Passport has all situations covered. This will ensure that you have no problem explaining what you do and donâ€™t eat, no matter where you are in the world.
When visiting a restaurant, show your waiter the relevant entry from this app, and ask them to read it.  Do not attempt to pronounce the text yourself!  If you are invited to a private home for a meal, show your host the relevant entry well in advance.
If booking a hotel by post or email, send a copy of the relevant page.  Please note that several languages may be used in the place you are visiting, so you may be able to offer the reader a choice of languages.
If all else fails then you can show them the images depicting what a vegan eats and what a vegan does not eat.
When booking flights then you can refer to the below airplane meal code to request a vegan meal when booking.
The Vegan Society is a registered charity and the oldest vegan society in the world, founded on 1 November 1944, in the UK by Donald Watson.
What do we want? Simple: a world where humans do not exploit non-human animals. A world where animals are free to exist in their own right. We promote a lifestyle that excludes, as far as possible and practical, all forms of exploitation of - and cruelty to - animals for the purposes of food, clothing or anything else.
We also want a just world for humans. A world where resources are utilised in a sustainable way to ensure all current and future generations are provided for - a world where no one goes hungry. At the heart of the sustainability and food justice agenda is plant-based food production and consumption: veganism.

title: In Sight - Norway+
description:
What is the name of the mountain you can see in the distance? What are the lakes you see in front of you? Point there with In Sight Norway+ and you'll see on the screen what they are called. See also places nearby with amazing high-resolution maps. High resolution offline maps of Norway are used down to a scale of 1:70 000.
Recommended by visitnorway.com 28/6 2014.
Also check out our new app "In Sight Svalbard" with completely offline high resolution maps.
* Offline Augmented Reality in Norway *
See what's near you where you travel in Norway: Mountains, Lakes, Places, Buildings, etc. You don't even have to be nearby Norway: You can manually set your location to a place in Norway to pretend you are there. Decide if you want to see places nearby, or famous cities around the world.
Works everywhere: By the sea, in the mountains, in the city. Without the internet, without coverage.
Turn the phone sideways to view on the camera screen the places that are nearby. Take a picture of what you see, and send it by email, or post it on facebook, directly from the App!
You can also add your own places!
In Sight Norway+ is also an altimeter, speedometer and also estimates the distance you've traveled. Choose between metric (km, meter) or imperial (miles, feet) units.
All data is built into the App, so you don't need internet. You only need internet when you use the map or send a picture on email or post it on facebook. High-resolution maps down to a scale of 1:70 000 donâ€™t require internet. For finer resolution internet is used.
Select between the following map types: Standard, Satellite, Hybrid, High Resolution and Sea Map. High resolution maps and sea maps are provided by the Norwegian Mapping Authority.
In Sight Norway+ relies on the compass and GPS of your device. Best results are achieved if you are outside.
COMPASS CALIBRATION AND ACCURACY.
One way to calibrate the compass is to move the phone in an 8-number manner 3 times: Once when the phone is in landscape, once in portrait and once facing up. Also stay away from magnetic sources that might influence the compass. For the compass to be accurate under usage, you have to be outside to get a good location reading.
Source: ws.geonames.org under the Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 License (http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/)
High resolution maps and sea maps from the Norwegian Mapping Authority (http://www.kartverket.no) are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 international (CC BY 4.0) (http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/deed.en)

title: Pyrenees Mountains
description:
More than 4000 peaks referenced in France, Spain and Andorra plus passes, lakes, shelters, villages, chapels, attractions and more.
When looking at the Pyrenees mountain range, who has not been eager to know the name of one of the summits that rises above the others? Now, this exceptional application allows you, in seconds, to find the peak's name, altitude and distance from you.
Aside from information about these summits, walkers, hikers and climbers will be able to locate shelters, cabins and the nearest shepherd tower or cave for shelter in case of bad weather. During excursions, hikes or climbs, you will also be able to find a lake or spring that will quench your thirst and fill your canteen.
Whether you are walking or driving, the app can guide you to nearby tourist attractions, the most visited sites, unique spots, picnic areas, scenic overlooks, megalithic ruins and villages.
Thanks to this application, you can even find places of worship, chapels and oratories at high altitudes.
All these attractions are also visible on the 2D map.
You can look up information on this app at any time, without an Internet connection.
Keep in mind that the accuracy with which the device locates  a peak or place of interest will depend on the device being used, the precision of your phone, and the place from which you are connecting. (See HELP).

title: Official Guide La Alhambra
description:
Download the Official Guide to the Alhambra in your mobile, prepare your visit and enjoy the most complete information while you explore the monument. Choose how you navigate: using the map, where you will find all the points of interest geolocated along with your position; or using the list of highlights that allows you to gradually discover each and every one of the secrets this monumental complex conceals.
You can explore the more than 655,000 sq. m of the Alhambra through the seven established routes included in the application or create your own customised route with your favourite locations. What is more, you can jot down anything that particularly grabs your attention by adding a note to your route and share all the information provided by the application on your networks.
Thanks to the more than 200 photographs â€“ including historical images by the great photographers of the Alhambra â€“ and tiered information, you can learn the most important facts while you are there and read about them in greater detail after your visit. If you are the kind who is fond of history, the Chronology section provides in-depth knowledge about the historical events that have occurred at the Alhambra over the centuries.
Donâ€™t miss any of the activities organised by the Council of the Alhambra â€“ the Agenda will keep you up to date. You will find all the details needed to plan your visit in the Information section: opening hours, ticket purchases, the weather in Granada, entrances, etc.
The application is available in Spanish and English.

title: Rocky Mountain National Park GyPSy Guide
description:
GyPSy Guide GPS driving tour of Rocky Mountain National Park is an excellent way to enjoy a sightseeing trip and to explore by driving yourself. There are 135+ audio points that play automatically, featuring what to see, stories, tips and advice. All the benefits of a guided tour, the freedom to drive yourself.
TOUR GUIDE AS YOU DRIVE AROUND ROCKY MOUNTAIN NATIONAL PARK
If you like driving yourself when you go sightseeing, GyPSy Guideâ„¢ tour apps allow you to enjoy a guided tour experience while remaining totally independent. By driving yourself, you'll be able to get from place to place faster, see more things and not be tied to anyone else's schedule.
DON'T MISS OUT ON THE BEST SIGHTS AND STORIES
The tour apps use your deviceâ€™s location abilities to play the commentary AUTOMATICALLY. All you have to do is drive, listen and decide which places you want to stop at. Our tour guides have created an insightful and entertaining tour of Rocky Mountain National Park. Weâ€™ll recommend the best places to experience and some great locations that most visitors will drive by.
PLAYS AUTOMATICALLY
GyPSy Guide knows where you are and which direction you are heading, and plays commentary automatically about the things you are seeing, plus stories and tips and advice.
EXPLORE LIKE A LOCAL
Itâ€™s just like having a local friend to show you around. And that friend just happens to be a professional tour guide.
GREAT VALUE
The same information you would get on a bus tour or from a guide book, for just a fraction of the price. And you control the itinerary and schedule.
WORKS OFFLINE
No data, cellular or even wireless network connection needed while touring. Download over Wi-Fi before you tour.  Anyone can use them with no need for roaming data â€“ even visiting from another country.
DRIVING TOUR ROUTE
Start the tour from either Estes Park or Grand Lake. The tour includes the most popular sightseeing places and much more:
1) Trail Ridge Road
2) Old Fall River Road
3) Alpine Visitor Center
4) Bear Lake
5) Horseshoe Park
6) Rock Cut
7) Gore Range Overlook
The tour is designed that you can drive it one way from either side or you can drive from one entrance to another and then back. The commentary provides all the major highlights each way, but different stories depending on which way you go.
NOTES
Download the app on Wi-Fi from your network at home or use any free Wi-Fi network. Because the app is filled with audio commentary and maps, its larger than "normal" apps.  Many phone/data networks may block the download because of size - so its important to download over a Wi-Fi network.
++  Continued use of GPS running in the background increases battery usage - we strongly recommend taking a cigarette style (DC outlet) car charger. This is much better than simply plugging into the USB port in a vehicle.
ABOUT US
GyPSy Guideâ„¢ produce award winning audio tours along scenic drives around the world.  Enjoyed by travelers who prefer to set their own pace and itinerary on vacation, but enjoy a fun, informative and educational guided experience.  Our goal is to provide a great introduction to the region and perhaps inspire you to learn more and return.  None of our apps include paid advertising or placements for benefit.

title: Regensburg Tourist City Tour
description:
The App "Regensburg Tourist Guide" makes it easy for you to discover the sights of the World Cultural Heritage on your own. With just a few clicks, you'll be guided through the city's tour, using interactive driving directions and Google Maps, from landmark to landmark. Once you have arrived, start the respective "listening" button and your journey into the past begins! For a better hearing experience, we recommend wearing a headphone.
NAVIGATION OPTIONAL
In order to find the individual sights, it is helpful to use the navigation of Google Maps. You will find them above the slide show of the attraction. Tap the button to open Google Navigation with the default destination. Since you are probably on foot, you should activate the pedestrian in the navigation of Google in the upper blue bar.
Note: Location approval is required for navigation. We, the developers and operators of the Regensburg Tourist App, do not track or store your location! However, when you open the navigation, you are on Google Maps and must agree to Google's terms of use. Roaming charges may also apply to your respective network provider, as data must be loaded from the network. You can request the respective costs from your network operator.
Please always pay attention to the traffic! The routes often lead over busy streets!
We wish you an exciting stay in Regensburg! Have a nice time!

Note: Location approval is required for navigation. We, the developers and operators of the Regensburg Tourist App, do not track or store your location! However, when you open the navigation, you are on Google Maps and must agree to Google\'s terms of use. Roaming charges may also apply to your respective network provider, as data must be loaded from the network. You can request the respective costs from your network operator.

Please always pay attention to the traffic! The routes often lead over busy streets!

We wish you an exciting stay in Regensburg! Have a nice time!'
recent_changes: Various bug fixes. Navigation now in your browser with Google - Maps

title: Camino PortuguÃ©s -Wise PIlgrim
description:
No Login Necessary.
Written for the 2018 season, making note of changes to the camino made within the last 12 months (there are quite a few).
The Camino Portugues App builds off of the success of the other Wise Pilgrim Guides, which are now in their 5th season... the original camino app.
This guide covers the route from Lisbon to Porto, and from Porto to Santiago de Compostela along the 'Central Way',  as well as the 'Coastal Route'.
Accommodation Directory:
A full directory of Albergues, camping, hotels, pensions, paradors, and cases rurales.  With special attention to those that can be booked online.
Stageless Guide:
No more "stage anxiety" or guide created bottlenecks.
Location Aware:
Every location is geo-coded.  Devices with GPS enabled will display actual distance from every point (albergue, church, city, etc.) within the app.  Devices without GPS will instead show measured distances between points.
Photos:
Photos of albergues, monuments and other points of interest along the way.  Currently 900+ images and growing.
Maps:
If you have a data connection, or are connected to wifi, you can view the locations of every point  on a map. Unfortunately, this feature is unavailable without a connection.
Scrollable Elevation Map:
This one is hard to show with just a screenshot, but the elevation that appears at the top of every city page scrolls East to West.  One complete elevation, from St. Jean Pied de Port to Santiago, uninterrupted by page folds.
Comments:
Albergue closed early for the season?  Have a restaurant that you want to share, or perhaps one to warn others about?  Every location in the app gives you the opportunity to leave a comment and to read the comments left by others. No registration necessary.
Â¡Buen Camino!

title: Radar Spotter AR pro
description:
It has never been easier to see what's going on overhead. All you have to do is pointing your phone to the plane in the sky like taking a photo to get all the detailed information about it.
Do you want to impress your friends? Do you want to know where this 9 o'clock flight you see every day is flying to? Are you an aviation enthusiast or a plane spotter who wants to see what flight will arrive next at the local airport? Then this tool is the right choice for you. It is useful for anyone who wants aircraft information instantly and it is surely a nice gag too.
There are various sites at the internet providing you with online radars. Why choose us?
We are the FASTEST, because we restrict to targets you can really spot at your location. As we do not deliver a huge amount of unnecessary data, we are also the LEANEST when it comes to bandwith consumption. We are focussed on usability, not on eye candy. No unnecessary clicks with our unique concept. We are the QUICKEST when the question comes to find the plane. What could be easier than pointing your phone to the aircraft you want details for? Last but not least augmented reality is a crucial part of the usability concept even available in the base version.
Need help? Visit our website www.radarworkx.com

title: TrekRight: Lycian Way
description:
TrekRight - Lycian Way is a comprehensive, incredibly handy mobile app for anyone walking all or part of the Lycian Way, Turkey's beautiful 400+ km / 250+ mi walk along the Turquoise Coast. This rugged, exhilarating walk is filled with stunning scenery, amazing ruins of ancient civilizations, incredibly friendly people, pristine beaches, delicious food, and more.
TrekRight includes detailed *offline* maps, handy reference information, comprehensive walking directions, and powerful location-aware functionality that enables you to simply enjoy your walk.
--- The Right Information, When You Need it ---
Location-aware information â€“ TrekRight provides you with information tailored to your current location. If you are approaching Kalkan, TrekRight will tell you how far you still have to go, what attractions are available around you, where you can find a water fountain, options for where to stay the night, easy access to interactive elevation profile charts, and clear, detailed directions. You can easily see what things you flagged as interesting, which things you added notes to, and which you marked as favorites. Real-time information that keeps you completely on top of things!
--- Trekopedia ---
TrekRightâ€™s â€˜Lycian Way Encyclopediaâ€™ is packed with extensive interactive reference information, organized into Communities, Accommodation, Attractions, Services, Points of Interest, Route Sections, and Articles. Everything can be searched and filtered, viewed on a map, notes can be added (anything from a simple reservation number to a copy-and-pasted blurb from a website), and more. Handy information (literally) at your fingertips!
--- Interactive Offline Maps ---
Powerful, flexible map built on top of our high-quality mapping engine, with full support for detailed *offline* map imagery. Displays your current location on your selected route along with pins showing all the locations included in the Trekopedia (just touch a pin to open its related Trekopedia entry). Our offline maps mean you donâ€™t require Internet access to use the mapping functionality. Online maps are also available for when you have an Internet connection. Easily filter and do searches. Scroll, zoom, and rotate the map. Completely transform how you â€˜seeâ€™ your surroundings on the Lycian Way.
--- Intelligent Compass ---
In addition to all the standard compass functionality, TrekRightâ€™s intelligent compass also points you in the right direction based on your current location and your selected route, and updates dynamically as you move. Two special compass indicators are available â€“ one points towards the end point of your current section (typically the next town on the route), and the other points which way you should go now, taking into consideration all the twists and turns in your route. Never get lost again!
--- Pre-Departure Planning & Preparation ---
TrekRight makes it easy to plan your route (including configuring the sections you want to follow), organize it into stages, and review distances and elevations (including a handy interactive Elevation Profile Chart). Comes pre-defined with popular routes (full and partial). Review and rank hotels / pensions, flag locations of interest as â€˜favoritesâ€™, add your own notes, and more. Be prepared!
--- Up-To-Date Content ---
TrekRightâ€™s content is regularly being updated and expanded based on the latest information available to us. You can check for content updates directly inside TrekRight and download our database whenever it is convenient for you (even on the trail), without having to connect to Google Play. Always be up to date!
--- No Internet Connection Required ---
All of TrekRight's content is stored directly on your phone, including our detailed offline maps. No Internet connection is required unless you want to use Google's online maps.

title: Vermont RT100 GyPSy Drive Tour
description:
Just like having a Tour Guide in your Carâ„¢!
Don't miss out on the best sights and things to do, on this scenic drive tour of Vermont's favorite drive - Route 100 Scenic Byway.  You can drive the tour either northbound or southbound.
*  Plays commentary AUTOMATICALLY as you drive
*  No Data or network connection required.  Works off-line
*  Prepared by Professional Tour Guides
*  300+ commentary points
*  Fraction of cost of bus tours or guide books.
Turn your phone or tablet into a Tour Guide and take your driving tours and sightseeing to a whole new level with the GyPSy Guideâ„¢ â€“ GPS Tour of Vermont's RT 100. Commentary plays AUTOMATICALLY as you drive so you don't miss any of the best sights and stories along the way.
This tour includes the most popular sightseeing stops and many more:
1) Covered Bridges
2) Waterfalls
3) Ben & Jerry's
4) Smugglers Notch
5) Vermont country Store
6) Calvin Coolidge Homestead
7) Von Trapp Family Lodge
Let GyPSy be your guide as it helps you work out the best places for you to visit by giving you helpful information so you can make good decisions and make the most of the time you have available.
** This app works OFF-LINE while you are touring.  There is no need to have a network or wireless connection while you are driving.
Once downloaded, this tour REQUIRES NO DATA to operate and activate, so you wonâ€™t incur roaming or data charges. YOU DO NOT REQUIRE A CELLULAR NETWORK CONNECTION TO TOUR!! You will not incur any data roaming charges to use this tour, even if you are from outside the USA.  Works Off-line and with Data Roaming turned OFF.
Professional tour guides have filled the guide with interesting and entertaining stories, loads of tips and advice on what to do and will point out places of interest as you approach them. There are 302 commentary points.
From the south, start the tour in Wilmington and continue all the way to Jeffersonville.
Form the north, start the tour in Jeffersonville and drive RT100 all the way to Wilmington.
BUT, you also can join ANYWHERE along the route.
Just download the app on Wi-Fi from your network at home, your resort or use any free Wi-Fi network. Because the app is filled with audio commentary and maps, its larger than "normal" apps.  Many phone/data networks will block the download because of size - so its IMPORTANT to download over a Wi-Fi network.
This tour is not just a directory but a designed tour to follow, just like how a tour guide would take you.  Itâ€™s simple and entertaining; just let GyPSy provide commentary automatically as you travel.  Itâ€™s just like driving around with a local expert.
Warning:  the tour suggests many great places to try Vermonts favorite culinary treats - bring your appetite.
++  Continued use of GPS running in the background increases battery usage - we strongly recommend taking a cigarette style (DC outlet) car charger.

title: Learn morrocan dialect:daRija
description:
You often travel to Morocco and want to know what the Moroccans tell when they talk to you, well this app is for you. It contains lots of English words translated in Moroccan dialect which is called Darija.
Morocco has two official languages: Arabic and Berber. Each language is spoken in different dialects, Classical Arabic is the language of administration.
Other languages â€‹â€‹such as French and Spanish, are also present in Morocco, while English is gaining ground in the world of business and international trade.
With this application, you will learn a lot of words and phrases that are pronounced frequently during your stay in Morocco.
It is also intended for adults and children who reside outside of Morocco and who do not have the chance to practice their native dialect.
The application is also helpful for the visitor to Algeria and Tunisia, as most of the Moroccan words are also used by the Algerian and Tunisian and vice versa.
The application contains the following menu:
- Help
- Letters to learn
- Usual words
- Greetings
- Personal pronouns
- Numbers
- Possessive pronouns
- Demonstrative Pronouns
- Family
- Colors
- Month, day, ...
- Members of the body
- Fruits and Vegetables
- Clothing
- Animals and insects
- Food
- The nature
- The house
- The kitchen
- Jobs and Trades
- The verb to have
- Test
- The grocer
- The doctor
- Visitors
- Customs
- Verbe to want
- Common phrases
- Time
A ios (for iPhone, iPad...) version is on the App Store.
A version in Spanish and Italian are also available.
Other words will be added in future versions. If you find any errors, please contact me, thank you and good Darija!

title: MyJourneys: Travel Logger & Tracker
description:
MyJourneys
is an incredible
travel app
that lets you easily capture all your travels and write your own travel diary of experiences. Log your travels and share travel experiences with friends!
Get your easy to use journey log and travel diary for all of your journeys tracking
EASILY LOG ALL YOUR TRAVELS
This travel app for Android users and travel addicts helps you easily capture all your travels. With this easy to use and fun travel log app, you will be able to write a diary for each trip you take, logging all your travel experiences. By using this incredible travel tracker app you'll never forget a trip and you'll know exactly when and how you experienced it. Easily enter all your travels in this travel diary and enjoy the memories directly on your phone whenever you want.
RECORDS YOUR EXPERIENCES, ADD PHOTOS & TEXTS
With the help of this travel journal, you will be able to record every travel experience, writing your own travel diary. title: Lycian Way Offline Maps
description:
This is a high-quality offline map for use with our TrailSmart: Great Trails of the World app.
It includes detailed coverage of the entire Lycian Way, plus good coverage of much of the surrounding region.
Maps can be zoomed in / out, scrolled, etc.  There's handy 3D shading / contour lines that provide a great perspective on the landscape.
Once downloaded, no Internet connection is required in TrailSmart.
*** Note that these maps require TrailSmart (available free). Simply download the map to your Android device and then run TrailSmart -- it'll recognize the map and you'll be able to use it.
Feedback about our maps is always welcomed and appreciated. Let us know how we can make them better serve your needs.
Tip: The file size for this map is very large (because of the 3D terrain / hill shading). Make sure you have a good WiFi connection when you download it as well as available space on your device. Maps can be deleted and re-installed as-needed if you need to temporarily free up space.

title: Australian Dump Points
description:
Australian Dump Points application once downloaded and installed on opening your phone's position is located on Google Maps, the closest open Caravan, Recreational Vehicle or Motorhome Effluent Dump Point is marked on the map, along with any others within a 500km distance.
Additional information displayed such as the distance to, the name, the street address (if available to allow you to use your GPS), if fees are applicable, what amenities, water, size restrictions and more.
Information shown will assist you to stay with the closest marked, or you can choose another and the directions to get there will be displayed, it also indicates if the location is open now, while still allowing you to plan your day.
All this without having to select additional buttons, or pay for in App purchases, with over 350 publicly available Effluent Dump Points across Australia, finding one in your time of need is as easy as this app.
All Locate by App Pty Ltd Applications are free from advertising, or tracking software.
We have endeavoured to get accurate information on locations and information on what is presented, we encourage you to help us maintain the accuracy and will update any information within a few days of receiving new information, contained within the app is a link that will allow the user to provide us feedback via a simple website form.     http://dump-points.com/appir.html or for new Dump Points  http://dump-points.com/new.html
We ask before you post a bad review to lets us know the problem so we can correct it, or if you are not satisfied with the quality of the app, we will refund you 100% of your cost if requested within 14 days of purchase.

title: Learn Japanese Pro Phrasebook
description:
The most easy to use mobile phrasebook aims at tourists and business people visiting Japan. Turn essential words and phrases into native voice which you can practice or play it to local people to get around with confidence.
Learn Japanese PRO is a paid app. If you want to try the free version please search for Learn Japanese Codegent on the store.
Features:
* Carefully translated list of essential phrases
* High quality audio pronunciation by native speaker
* Play all phrases automatically in each category
* 900+ phrases in 18 categories
* Ability to adjust font size
* No internet connection required
* Highlight important words with tips
* Store frequently used phrases in favourites
* Search by keywords
* No adverts or annoying popups

* Shopping

title: Wisely : Camino FrancÃ©s
description:
Welcome to Wisely!
Built from the same up to date database as the other Wise Pilgrim Apps and Guidebooks, 'Wisely' was designed to fill the two most requested needs for pilgrims:
Offline Mapping:  Download the maps to your phone while you have an internet connection, and enjoy them while you are on the trail.  The offline maps are designed for the outdoors and are rendered to show the elevation changes along the route.  Map markers include all cities, 900+ accommodation options, notable landmarks along the way, and notices about deviations and alternative routes along the way.  A click on the pin brings up a description of the route, distances, services available in any given place and accommodation details.
Online Booking:  Making reservations for the night is now much easier.  Every city that has a bookable place to sleep includes a direct link on booking.com.  Likewise, every accommodation option that is bookable online includes one as well.  Finding a place to sleep, and finding it on the map, just got a whole lot easier.
Please note that this app requires the additional download of the maps, which are about 200mb in size.  There is no way around this, an offline map is an offline map.
Also, note that this app is in rapid development.  This means that updates to it will be frequent over the next 6-12 months as minor bugs are squashed and features are added.  These updates will NOT require you to re-download the maps.  They will deliver additional content and features.
Please remember that this is version 1 of the 'Wisely' series of Mapping and Booking apps.  Go gentle on the reviews and please please please send me bug reports so that the app can be made better.  You're the best!
No In-App Purchase.  No signup.  Just goodness.

description_html:
b'Runt om i landet finns drygt 350 rastplatser som f\xc3\xb6rvaltas och sk\xc3\xb6ts p\xc3\xa5 uppdrag av Trafikverket.

Standard och utrustning \xc3\xa4r lite olika p\xc3\xa5 de olika rastplatserna, men det gemensamma f\xc3\xb6r dem \xc3\xa4r att du ska kunna anv\xc3\xa4nda dem oavsett om du har n\xc3\xa5got funktionshinder eller inte. H\xc3\xa4r finns ocks\xc3\xa5 toaletter, informationstavlor, sittplatser med bord och soptunnor.

Trafikverkets rastplatser \xc3\xa4r inte till f\xc3\xb6r l\xc3\xa5ngtidsuppst\xc3\xa4llda husbilar och husvagnar (och d\xc3\xa4rf\xc3\xb6r de oftast inte kan anv\xc3\xa4ndas som st\xc3\xa4llplatser) utan f\xc3\xb6r trafikanter som stannar en stund och kopplar av.

Planera din resa och bes\xc3\xb6k n\xc3\xa5gon av landets vackra rastplatser och utnyttja m\xc3\xb6jligheten till en paus p\xc3\xa5 resan. H\xc3\xa4r kan du se var trafikverkets rastplatser finns, vilken standard de har och vilken service erbjuds.

Rastplatserna ser olika ut, men gemensamt \xc3\xa4r att alla ska vara anpassade b\xc3\xa5de f\xc3\xb6r personer med och utan funktionshinder. Vanligtvis finns informationstavlor, bord och b\xc3\xa4nkar f\xc3\xb6r att trafikanterna ska kunna \xc3\xa4ta medhavd f\xc3\xa4rdkost och m\xc3\xb6jlighet att sl\xc3\xa4nga sopor fr\xc3\xa5n resan. Dessutom brukar det finnas toaletter. P\xc3\xa5 en del finns \xc3\xa4ven m\xc3\xb6jlighet att t\xc3\xb6mma l\xc3\xb6sa latriner. Ibland finns restaurang och bensinstation med mera n\xc3\xa4ra rastplatsen, men de r\xc3\xa4knas inte alltid som tillh\xc3\xb6rande rastplatsen, utan \xc3\xa4r rent privata anl\xc3\xa4ggningar. Rastplatserna ska ocks\xc3\xa5 sk\xc3\xb6tas om regelbundet. P\xc3\xa5 rastplatsbyggnaden finns en skylt, d\xc3\xa4r entrepren\xc3\xb6ren ska anteckna senaste st\xc3\xa4dtidpunkt och signera vem som utf\xc3\xb6rt st\xc3\xa4dningen.

Ett finmaskigt n\xc3\xa4t av trygga rastplatser med god kapacitet, r\xc3\xa4tt funktionalitet och i gott skick ger f\xc3\xb6ruts\xc3\xa4ttning f\xc3\xb6r yrkeschauff\xc3\xb6rer att kunna utf\xc3\xb6ra effektiva transporter inom ramen f\xc3\xb6r lagstadgade k\xc3\xb6r- och vilotider. F\xc3\xb6r yrkeschauff\xc3\xb6rer \xc3\xa4r v\xc3\xa4gen och dess sidoanl\xc3\xa4ggningar s\xc3\xa5som rastplatser sj\xc3\xa4lvklart viktig del av arbetsmilj\xc3\xb6n, \xc3\xa4ven om arbetsgivaren inte r\xc3\xa5der \xc3\xb6ver den. D\xc3\xa4rf\xc3\xb6r st\xc3\xa4lls h\xc3\xb6gre krav p\xc3\xa5 rastplatser utifr\xc3\xa5n yrkeschauff\xc3\xb6rers behov (till exempel sanit\xc3\xa4rt) \xc3\xa4n f\xc3\xb6r hobbytrafikanters behov.

Bra rastplatser inbjuder till n\xc3\xb6dv\xc3\xa4ndiga stopp f\xc3\xb6r vila och rekreation. Tr\xc3\xb6tthet vid ratten \xc3\xa4r en vanlig olycksfaktor n\xc3\xa4stan att j\xc3\xa4mf\xc3\xb6ra med olyckor relaterade till alkohol. S\xc3\xa5 om n\xc3\xa5got inte st\xc3\xa4mmer \xc3\xb6verens med hur det borde vara, om du f\xc3\xa5r n\xc3\xa5got problem p\xc3\xa5 rastplatsen, rapportera v\xc3\xa4nligen till geoinfo.apps@gmail.com och/eller direkt till Trafikverkets kundtj\xc3\xa4nst (Telefon: 0771-921 921).

Fr\xc3\xa5gor och svar om rastplatser:

1. Vem ansvarar f\xc3\xb6r informationstavlorna p\xc3\xa5 rastplatserna?
- Det \xc3\xa4r Trafikverket som ansvarar f\xc3\xb6r informationstavlorna. De ska vara tillg\xc3\xa4ngliga \xc3\xa5ret runt, \xc3\xa4ven f\xc3\xb6r personer med funktionshinder. P\xc3\xa5 en del rastplatser har kommunen f\xc3\xa5tt tillst\xc3\xa5nd att s\xc3\xa4tta upp kartor och information om bes\xc3\xb6ksm\xc3\xa5l i n\xc3\xa4rheten.

2. Hur ofta ska toaletterna st\xc3\xa4das?
- Tillsyn, st\xc3\xa4dning och sk\xc3\xb6tsel av rastplats och toaletter ska utf\xc3\xb6ras tv\xc3\xa5 g\xc3\xa5nger per dygn, en g\xc3\xa5ng mellan klockan 6 och 10 och en g\xc3\xa5ng mellan klockan 15 och 20 alla dagar under perioden 1 juni\xe2\x80\x9331 augusti och en g\xc3\xa5ng per dygn \xc3\xb6vrig tid av \xc3\xa5ret.P\xc3\xa5 rastplatsbyggnaden finns en skylt, d\xc3\xa4r entrepren\xc3\xb6ren ska anteckna senaste st\xc3\xa4dtidpunkt och signera vem som har st\xc3\xa4dat.

3. Varf\xc3\xb6r g\xc3\xa5r det inte att t\xc3\xb6mma en fast latrin p\xc3\xa5 rastplatserna?
- P\xc3\xa5 rastplatskartan kan du se vilka rastplatser som har latrint\xc3\xb6mning. De anl\xc3\xa4ggningar som finns \xc3\xa4r bara avsedda f\xc3\xb6r l\xc3\xb6sa latriner. P\xc3\xa5 st\xc3\xb6rre campingplatser och p\xc3\xa5 en del bensinmackar g\xc3\xa5r det att t\xc3\xb6mma fasta latriner.

4. G\xc3\xa5r det att t\xc3\xb6mma gr\xc3\xa5vatten och l\xc3\xb6sa latriner p\xc3\xa5 alla rastplatser?
- Nej, gr\xc3\xa5vatten kan du inte t\xc3\xb6mma alls. Det f\xc3\xa5r inte blandas med latrint\xc3\xb6mning.

5. Hur l\xc3\xa4nge f\xc3\xa5r man st\xc3\xa5 med sin husvagn eller husbil p\xc3\xa5 en rastplats?
- V\xc3\xa5ra rastplatser \xc3\xa4r fr\xc3\xa4mst avsedda f\xc3\xb6r tillf\xc3\xa4llig rast och vila, inte f\xc3\xb6r \xc3\xb6vernattning. P\xc3\xa5 rastplatser och skyltade P-platser \xc3\xa4r det dock i grunden till\xc3\xa5tet att st\xc3\xa5 h\xc3\xb6gst 24 timmar.'

title: Explore Skye - Visitors Guide
description:
Explore Skye aims to help visitors get the most out of their time on Skye. The app was developed using first-hand local knowledge and provides GPS navigation links, professional photos and will work without phone signal.
Included in the app are sections on the the Outdoors, Viewpoints, Beaches, Castles, Boat Trips, Activities and Practical Information. Each listing has a selection of photos to browse through as well as useful hints and tips to make the most of your visit.
The Isle of Skye is renowned as one of the worlds top tourist destinations. Easily accessible from the Scottish mainland via the picturesque Skye bridge there is something here for everyone. Whether its the rugged landscape of the Cuilin mountains, the eerie beauty of the Quiraing or the historic castles, Skye will not disappoint. With the Explore Skye App, you can have all the essential information on Skye at your fingertips.

title: Turbulence Meter
description:
Afraid of flying?
Turbulence Meter allows you to take control of the situation, to be aware of reality during flight and turbulence periods.
Using the accelerometer of your smartphone, Turbulence Meter shows the strength of the encountered turbulence in offline mode. Having objective information about the encountered turbulence will allow you to control your fear.
On the ground or in flight you can also review the Frequently Asked Questions regarding turbulence and watch a video explaining those unpleasant moments. Before the flight you can also check the turbulence forecast chart (at the moment covering Europe, North Africa and one part of the Middle East).
FEATURES:
- real-time turbulence meter
- turbulence forecast map
- turbulence facts

title: Camino del Norte -Wise Pilgrim
description:
No account necessary.  No hidden costs.
Now in their 6th year as a mobile app, and their 9th online, the Wise Pilgrim Guides are the go-to source of up-to-date information on the Camino de Santiago.
The app is updated regularly with new content and new features.
This guide covers the Camino del Norte from Irun to Santiago, the most popular route across Spain. It has been redesigned and now works almost exclusively offline.  To use the map features, or to share your comments with other guide owners, will require a data connection.  As more an more albergues share their WiFi this becomes less of an issue, and the guide will tell you which ones offer WiFi.
Accommodation Directory:
A full directory of Albergues, camping, hotels, pensions, paradors, and cases rurales with special attention to those that can be booked online.
Stageless Guide:
No more "stage anxiety" or guide created bottlenecks.
Location Aware:
Every location is geo-coded.  Devices with GPS enabled will display actual distance from every point (albergue, church, city, etc.) within the app.  Devices without GPS will instead show measured distances between points.
Photos:
Photos of albergues, monuments and other points of interest along the way.  Currently 900+ images and growing.
Maps:
If you have a data connection, or are connected to wifi, you can view the locations of every point  on a map. Unfortunately, this feature is unavailable without a connection.
Scrollable Elevation Map:
This one is hard to show with just a screenshot, but the elevation that appears at the top of every city page scrolls East to West.  One complete elevation, from St. Jean Pied de Port to Santiago, uninterrupted by page folds.
Comments:
Albergue closed early for the season?  Have a restaurant that you want to share, or perhaps one to warn others about?  Every location in the app gives you the opportunity to leave a comment and to read the comments left by others. No registration necessary.
Â¡Buen Camino and thank you for your support!

As more an more albergues share their WiFi this becomes less of an issue, and the guide will tell you which ones offer WiFi.

title: Learn Korean Pro - Phrasebook
description:
Learn Korean is an easy to use mobile Korean Phrasebook that will give visitors to Korea and those who are interested in learning Korean a good start in the language.
Learn Korean is recorded using native speaker and we have tried our best to be authentic in the pronunciation whilst ensuring it is easy to understand. Recommended app for tourists and business people visiting Korea.
We recommend you to use Wi-Fi connection the first time to download the database.
Features
* Carefully translated list of essential phrases
* High quality audio pronunciation by native speaker
* Play all phrases automatically in each category
* 900+ phrases in 18 categories
* Ability to adjust font size
* No internet connection required
* Highlight important words with tips
* Store frequently used phrases in favourites
* Search by keywords
* No adverts or annoying popups
Categories:
* Greetings
* General conversation
* Numbers
* Directions and places
* Transportation
* Eating out
* Accommodation
* Time and date
* Shopping
* Colours
* Towns and provinces
* Countries
* Tourist attractions
* Family
* Dating
* Emergency
* Feeling sick
* Tongue twisters
FEEDBACK
If you like this app and find it useful please take a few seconds to give us a rating in the Android Market. For comments and suggestions please send an email to apps@codegent.com. We love getting feedback from users of our apps.
Follow us on twitter : http://www.twitter.com/codegentapps

title: Airline Flight Status Tracker & Trip Planning
description:
âœˆ FlightHero is a flight-tracking app that provides a real time flight status information and helps you to know flight status, lets you to track a flight. Aware of the fact that is also shows a real time flight-board with arrivals and departures, airport traffic delays and a current airport weather in addition to a 15 day detailed weather forecast and synchronizes with your TripIt account (via In-App TripIt Sync AddOn).
Why we asking you to give a FligthHero special permissions?
- Identity: Used for implementing a user account functionality for saving your flight related data such as favorite flights, favorite accounts and your customized settings.
- Calendar: Used for synchronizing your upcoming fligths with a calendar of your choose so that you won't miss the flight (optional)
- Location: Used for determing nearest airports to you and planes nearby.
- Photos/Media/Files: Used for viewing your stored boarding passes in the app and for moving a FligthHero app to an SD card (optional)
- Camera: For making pictures of your boarding passes
- WiFi connection information: Used to understand whether your WiFi is ON or OFF
- Device and call information: Used for ability to send a text message with flight status
FlightHero has been positively mentioned by Forbes, WSJ, CNN.
These features let FlightHero to be one of the best travel apps:
âœˆ THE LARGEST COVERAGE FOR THE FLIGHTS, AIRPORTS AND AIRLINES
- 1550 airlines: commercial, cargo, charters
- 17000 airports around the world, including:
â€¢ USA (5639)
- Find closest airports to you within 140 miles (200 km)
âœˆ REAL TIME FLIGHT BOARD WITH ARRIVALS AND DEPARTURES
- Refreshes regualarly with the ability to cache data when there is no internet connection available
- Advances sorting order
- Advanced filters: airlines, statuses, arrival and departure information and time range for the most effective sky scanning
- 3 days (72 hours) time interval for arrivals and departures
âœˆ FLIGHT STATUS
- Actual position of the aircraft for the most accurate flight control. Use it as your personal virtual flight radar to know the aircraft speed, latitude, longitude and the altitude
âœˆ FLIGHT ALERTS via PUSH NOTIFICATIONS including:
- Status confirmation prior to departure
- Notification if the flight is delayed
- Notification if the flight is canceled or diverted
- Arrival notification when the flight lands
âœˆ AIRPORT WEATHER AND TRAFFIC DELAYS
- 15 day detailed weather forecast helps you stay dry when you grab your kayak for fishing on vacation
- Delay on a 5-point scale with the 0.25 step
- Actual Temperature
- Wind speed and direction
âœˆ SHARE INFORMATION ON FLIGHT STATUS
- SMS
- Email
- Twitter
- Facebook
âœˆ TERMINAL PLANS AND SEAT MAPS
- Download all at once from the "Additional Content". Available only for major terminals
âœˆ SEARCH
- By number
- By route
- Indirect flights
- Recently Used list
âœˆ FAVORITES
- Add Flights by swiping from the right to the left
- Add Airports
âœˆ TripIt SYNC
- Synchronization with your TripIt account (Available through In-App)
âœˆ SERVICES
- Browse hotels via Booking.com
- Car hire via RentalCars.com
- Integrated with Foursquare
- Radar shows nearest airports and flights
âœˆ MULTILINGUAL
â€¢ 29 Languages
â€¢ 4U 9525 Germanwings Barcelona Duesseldorf A320
âœˆ UNIVERSAL APP
- Single version for Android Phones and Tablets

title: Normandy D-Day 1944
description:
This is the essential app for visiting the Normandy invasion beaches and the many sites of interest further inland. Normandy D-Day 1944 covers 100 locations, including the five invasion beaches, with 500 photographs from Utah Beach to Sword Beach, from the Merville Battery in the east to the Azeville Battery in the west.
It will help guide you to some of the amazing sites of interest - from bunkers and batteries to the more major sites like the American Cemetery at Colleville-sur-Mer, and the amazing Pegasus Memorial Park, commemorating the British 6th Airborne. The app contains a wealth of practical and useful information for any traveller including museums, opening hours, toilets, etc which will help you plan your visit to this beautiful part of France.
*100 locations throughout Normandy
*500 photographs
*20 Museums
*7 countries represented over 100 locations
*Offering an historical guide to the D-Day landings, from the preparation to the breakout from Normandy
*Every location has been visited, extensively researched and photographed by Spot On Locations
*Content written by professional journalists with specialist background in battlefield tourism
*Fully researched, concise history on each beach landing - Utah, Omaha, Gold, Juno and Sword
*Fully researched concise history on Operations Overlord, Neptune, Titanic, Jupiter, Goodwood, Bluecoat and Cobra
*All locations have also been categorised into 5 colour coded groups:
Cemeteries
Battlegrounds
Memorials
Museums
Historical Interest
*Colour-coded pins (showing different location â€˜typesâ€™ e.g. Cemeteries, Museums, Historical Interest, etc)
*GPS co-ordinates
*2 ways to view the map either by colour code or by flag pins
Normandy D-Day 1944 is packed full of information, facts and stories of the ordinary soldier - the first Victoria Cross recipient, the first Medal of Honor recipient, the first British soldier killed on D-Day, the paratrooper who was buried with his dog, the first mass celebrated in an unoccupied France, the first radio recording by the British Broadcasting Corporation of church bells peeling out for freedom, stories of the horror that unfolded on Omaha Beach and stories of ordinary men doing extraordinary feats.
This app is a great way to learn about all aspects of the Normandy landings and the breakout which eventually lead to the liberation of Europe.
Features
-Zoom to specific site locations
-Each location is colour coded and shown in List view as well as the Map view
-Colour-coded pins (showing different location â€˜typesâ€™ e.g. Cemeteries, Museums, etc)
-Facility to toggle pin views between colour pins and flag pins
-Each location can also be viewed as a flag pin and is shown also in Access & Facilities page
-Favourites list page to shortlist your locations, helping you to plan your battlefield tour
-Favourites map page to show your locations, helping you to plan your battlefield tour
-Incredibly easy to navigate around the map
-GPS positions included for individual sites
-Photos can also be viewed in landscape and are zoomable
-Additional navigation facility available using online maps (Roaming charges may apply for this feature)

title: Japanese Food Dictionary
description:
Assume you don't know the Japanese language, when you go to the Japanese restaurant and realize that the menu does not contain any pictures and English, and you donâ€™t know how to order the food, this App can help you!
"Japanese Food Dictionary" collects hundred of Japanese food, provide the translation, picture and pronunciation.
You can use this App offline,  network access is not required.
You can:
- find the food by restaurant
- find the food by food category
- search by Japanese keyword (Japanese input is included)
- search by English keyword
- save the food to "Favorites"  (Limit:999)
- add the food to the order list, (call the waiter), in â€œMy order listâ€, play the Japanese pronunciation, which can help you ordering food easily.

title: Jasper National Park GyPSy Tour
description:
Just like having a Tour Guide in your Carâ„¢!
GyPSy Guide GPS driving tour of Jasper National Park is a great way to the experience the Rockies biggest national park. There are 108 audio points that play automatically, featuring what to see, stories, tips and advice. All the benefits of a guided tour, the freedom to drive yourself.
TOUR GUIDE AS YOU DRIVE THE ROCKIES
If you like driving yourself when you go sightseeing, GyPSy Guideâ„¢ tour apps allow you to enjoy a guided tour experience while remaining totally independent. By driving yourself, you'll be able to get from place to place faster, see more things and not be tied to anyone else's schedule.
DON'T MISS OUT ON THE BEST SIGHTS AND STORIES
The tour apps use your deviceâ€™s location abilities to play the commentary AUTOMATICALLY. All you have to do is drive, listen and decide which places you want to stop at. Our tour guides have created insightful and entertaining tours of the Rockies. Weâ€™ll recommend the best places to see and some great locations that most visitors don't get to see.
PLAYS AUTOMATICALLY
GyPSy Guide knows where you are and which direction you are heading, and plays commentary automatically about the things you are seeing, plus stories and tips and advice.
EXPLORE LIKE A LOCAL
Itâ€™s just like having a local friend to show you around. And that friend just happens to be a professional tour guide.
GREAT VALUE
The same information you would get on a bus tour or from a guide book, for just a fraction of the price. And you control the itinerary and schedule.
WORKS OFFLINE
No data, cellular or even wireless network connection needed while touring. Download over Wi-Fi before you tour.  Anyone can use them with no need for roaming data â€“ even visiting from another country.
DRIVING TOUR ROUTE
The tour includes the most popular sightseeing stops and many more:
1) Maligne Canyon
2) Maligne Lake
3) Miette Hotsprings
4) Pyramid Lake
5) Jasper Tramway
6) Old Fort Point
7) Jasper Park Lodge
You can join the tour anywhere along the route. A good place to start is from in the town of Jasper. If staying at the Jasper Park Lodge, you will join the tour as you exit the lodge.
CANADIAN ROCKIES APP BUNDLE
This tour is a part of a set of tour apps by GyPSy Guide to explore the Canadian Rockies National Parks. Other tours in the series include:
*  Banff Townsite Tour
*  Banff Lake Louise Yolo
*  Icefields Parkway
*  And Calgary to Banff (Free)
NOTES
Download the app on Wi-Fi from your network at home or use any free Wi-Fi network. Because the app is filled with audio commentary and maps, its larger than "normal" apps.  Many phone/data networks may block the download because of size - so its important to download over a Wi-Fi network.
++  Continued use of GPS running in the background increases battery usage - we strongly recommend taking a cigarette style (DC outlet) car charger. This is much better than simply plugging into the USB port in a vehicle.
ABOUT US
GyPSy Guideâ„¢ produce award winning audio tours along scenic drives around the world.  Enjoyed by travelers who prefer to set their own pace and itinerary on vacation, but enjoy a fun, informative and educational guided experience.  Our goal is to provide a great introduction to the region and perhaps inspire you to learn more and return.  None of our apps include paid advertising or placements for benefit.

Download the app on Wi-Fi from your network at home or use any free Wi-Fi network. Because the app is filled with audio commentary and maps, its larger than "normal" apps. Many phone/data networks may block the download because of size - so its important to download over a Wi-Fi network.

++ Continued use of GPS running in the background increases battery usage - we strongly recommend taking a cigarette style (DC outlet) car charger. This is much better than simply plugging into the USB port in a vehicle.


ABOUT US

GyPSy Guide\xe2\x84\xa2 produce award winning audio tours along scenic drives around the world. Enjoyed by travelers who prefer to set their own pace and itinerary on vacation, but enjoy a fun, informative and educational guided experience. Our goal is to provide a great introduction to the region and perhaps inspire you to learn more and return. None of our apps include paid advertising or placements for benefit.'

title: Guthook's Long Trail Guide
description:
Guthook's Long Trail Guide is a detailed, map-based smartphone guide for your hike on the 270-mile Long Trail. It maps and lists more than 500 important hiker waypoints along the LT such as water sources, shelters, tenting sites, road crossings, resupply locations, and may others.
Key features:
- No mobile or internet connection is required after initial setup -- works in Airplane Mode
- Detailed maps with your GPS location
- Elevation profile view
- Custom route creator
- Multiple offline map choices
- Real-time comments from other hikers
- Send your current location to friends or family via text message or email
The guidebook lists every waypoint in order by distance along the trail and how far away you are from each waypoint. The guidebook also includes a detailed town guide for major resupply points, towns, and services along the Long Trail.
Waypoint details include:
- Mileage point and elevation
- Photographs
- Distance to the next water source and tent site
- Comments section where you may post comments and read other hikersâ€™ comments
Types of waypoints:
- Water sources (including the reliability of each water source)
- Detailed resupply and town information:
- post offices and other package services
- restaurants
- grocery stores and convenience stores
- gear shops and hardware stores
- laundromats
- lodging, public showers, public restrooms
- public libraries
- Tenting sites/camping sites
- Trail junctions
- Parking areas along the trail
- Picnic areas, campgrounds, ranger stations
- Roads, railroad tracks, power lines, fences, gates
- Natural landmarks (e.g. mountain passes)
- Privies/restrooms
- Views
About the Long Trail*: The Long Trail, or LT, is the original and oldest long distance hiking trail in the United States. The 273-mile trail crosses south-to-north through the state of Vermont along the Green Mountains, from the Massachusetts border to the Canada border. The first 107 miles of the trail overlaps the famous Appalachian Trail. Countless hikers enjoy hiking anywhere from a few miles to the entire trail each year.
*"Long Trail" is a registered trademark of the Green Mountain Club

title: London Travel Pro - Bus & Tube
description:
A simple yet powerful journey planning application to assist you in your travels in and around London's transport network.
Utilising live data, you'll be provided with up-to-the-minute journey information covering departures, arrivals and service status for:
- London Buses
- London Underground
- Docklands Light Railway (DLR)
- London Overground
- TfL Rail (soon to be Crossrail)
- London River Services (Thames Clippers)
- Santander Cycles
Main Features:
- Intuitive map interface
- Officially licensed Tube Map
- Home screen widgets allowing easy access to arrivals at your favourite stop
- Customisable app and map themes
- Easy to use favourites and nearby locations
- Live arrivals, service status and route information for all suburban TfL services
- Journey Planner with walking directions, accessibility options and mode selection
- Live cycle hire data
- Footage from TfL CCTV traffic cameras
- Filter routes and lines to ignore the ones you don't use
If you have any comments, questions or issues, please contact routemaster20@gmail.com.
Want to test the latest version? Join the beta programme at https://play.google.com/apps/testing/com.toson.londontransport.

title: Flight Information Global Pro
description:
Easy to use app that shows airport and flight information for nearly 5000 airports across the globe.
- Coverage of nearly 5000 airports from all over the globe.
- Flight arrivals and departures information
- Flight status (delayed. cancelled, on-time etc.)
- Details of airport departure gates, baggage claim (where available)
- Indoor airport maps (both Google Indoor Maps and OpenStreetMaps)
- Details of facilities in the airport (bars, cafes, shops etc. Power by Google Places).
- Taxi information, Uber and Hailo integration
- Hotel Booking

title: Grand Teton GyPSy Drive Tour
description:
GyPSy Guide GPS driving tour of Grand Teton is an excellent way to enjoy a sightseeing trip to explore the national park. There are 160+ audio points that play automatically, featuring what to see, stories, tips and advice. All the benefits of a guided tour, the freedom to drive yourself.
TOUR GUIDE AS YOU DRIVE AROUND GRAND TETON NATIONAL PARK
If you like driving yourself when you go sightseeing, GyPSy Guideâ„¢ tour apps allow you to enjoy a guided tour experience while remaining totally independent. By driving yourself, you'll be able to get from place to place faster, see more things and not be tied to anyone else's schedule.
DON'T MISS OUT ON THE BEST SIGHTS AND STORIES
The tour apps use your deviceâ€™s location abilities to play the commentary AUTOMATICALLY. All you have to do is drive, listen and decide which places you want to stop at. Our tour guides have created an insightful and entertaining tour of Grand Teton. Weâ€™ll recommend the best places to experience and some great locations that most visitors will drive by.
PLAYS AUTOMATICALLY
GyPSy Guide knows where you are and which direction you are heading, and plays commentary automatically about the things you are seeing, plus stories and tips and advice.
EXPLORE LIKE A LOCAL
Itâ€™s just like having a local friend to show you around. And that friend just happens to be a professional tour guide.
GREAT VALUE
The same information you would get on a bus tour or from a guide book, for just a fraction of the price. And you control the itinerary and schedule.
WORKS OFFLINE
No data, cellular or even wireless network connection needed while touring. Download over Wi-Fi before you tour.  Anyone can use them with no need for roaming data â€“ even visiting from another country.
DRIVING TOUR ROUTE
The tour includes the most popular sightseeing stops and many more:
1) Jenny Lake and Jackson Lake Area
2) Snake River and eastern highway side
3) Colter Bay and north end of park
4) Moose area
5) Moose Wilson Corridor
You can join the tour from any of the 4 park entrances or anywhere along the route. Many people start in the town of Jackson or start the tour as they are leaving Yellowstone.
NOTES
Download the app on Wi-Fi from your network at home or use any free Wi-Fi network. Because the app is filled with audio commentary and maps, its larger than "normal" apps.  Many phone/data networks may block the download because of size - so its important to download over a Wi-Fi network.
++  Continued use of GPS running in the background increases battery usage - we strongly recommend taking a cigarette style (DC outlet) car charger. This is much better than simply plugging into the USB port in a vehicle.
ABOUT US
GyPSy Guideâ„¢ produce award winning audio tours along scenic drives around the world.  Enjoyed by travelers who prefer to set their own pace and itinerary on vacation, but enjoy a fun, informative and educational guided experience.  Our goal is to provide a great introduction to the region and perhaps inspire you to learn more and return.  None of our apps include paid advertising or placements for benefit.

title: E-walk - Offline maps
description:
E-WALK
E-walk allows you to download offline maps, to plan your treks, to show and share your position, to record your treks, etc... This makes E-walk the perfect companion for outdoors activities (such as trekking, hiking, fishing, hunting, etc...) and for traveling abroad, because you can fully use it offline.
Lost in a forest? E-walk brings you back to your car. Forgot about where was this lovely boutique you noticed last year in Venice? E-walk refreshes your memory!
E-WALK KEY FEATURES
â€¢ download maps for later offline use
â€¢ show your current location on the map
â€¢ search places (last searches are saved for offline use)
â€¢ record your treks
â€¢ select different base maps (streets, satellite, terrain, etc...)
â€¢ plan your treks by creating and editing KML files on the map. A KML file can contains markers, lines & polygons
E-WALK ADVANCED FEATURES
â€¢ organize your treks in folders & subfolders
â€¢ display overlay maps (weather, roads, metro/bus, ski slopes, sea map, etc...)
â€¢ share your position via e-mail or SMS
â€¢ open a position in your other geo apps (such as Google Maps, Waze, TomTom, Sygic, Mappy, Locus, Orux, MyTrails, etc...)
â€¢ share a trek by e-mail, bluetooth, etc... Either in KML file format (by default) or in GPX file format
â€¢ import GPX files (they will be converted in KMZ format)
â€¢ add custom maps in the XYZ protocol (see
http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Slippy_map_tilenames
)
â€¢ add custom maps in the WMS protocol (version 1.1.1 & 1.3.0 are supported, Web Mercator coordinate system only. See
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_Map_Service
)
E-WALK FREE
Want to try first? Get
E-walk Free
!
E-WALK PLUGINS
Some plugins are available for E-walk (a plugin is an app that adds features to another app). You can download them here:
â€¢
IGN maps
: this plugin adds maps provided by the french national institute of geographical and forestry information (
http://www.ign.fr
). These maps are the same as the ones used by the GÃ©oportail website (
http://www.geoportail.gouv.fr
). The plugin also allows you to use the IGN Leisure Space (
https://ignrando.fr
). It is a website providing points of interest and treks that you can synchronize on your device.
â€¢
ONCFS maps
: this plugin adds maps provided by the french national office for wildlife and hunting (
http://www.oncfs.gouv.fr
)
CONTACT
A problem with E-walk? A suggestion? A feedback? Please do not hesitate to send an e-mail to
contact@ewalk.app
!

These maps are the same as the ones used by the G\xc3\xa9oportail website (http://www.geoportail.gouv.fr). The plugin also allows you to use the IGN Leisure Space (https://ignrando.fr). It is a website providing points of interest and treks that you can synchronize on your device.
\xe2\x80\xa2 ONCFS maps: this plugin adds maps provided by the french national office for wildlife and hunting (http://www.oncfs.gouv.fr)

CONTACT

A problem with E-walk? A suggestion? A feedback? Please do not hesitate to send an e-mail to contact@ewalk.app !'

title: Maps Altimeter
description_html:
b'Maps Altimeter shows your current altitude in Google Maps or any other app, like TomTom, Sygic, CoPilot, Skobbler, WhatsApp, Chrome. It automatically detects when Google Maps or any other app of your choice is active and shows an elegant overlay with a altimeter. It is also possible to show the altimeter when you connect to an Bluetooth device.

FEATURES:
- No advertisements!
- No internet access necessary, no backdoors sharing your private information;
- It automatically shows and hides, depending whether Google Maps (or any other app of your choice) is active or not;
- It automatically shows and hides, depending whether a Bluetooth connection is active;
- There is also a manual mode, to control it via the notification bar manually;
- Choose between meters and feet (m and ft);
- Hide it for 10 seconds by touching the overlay;
- Adjustable transparency;
- Adjustable size;
- Adjustable colors;
- Adjustable text styles;
- Adjustable position, just drag it anywhere you like;
- Can be used with any app installed on your device

CONTACT US:
Please contact us if this application does not work properly on your device.
We will try to fix the problem for the next release.

This app uses Accessibility services. This app will only use Accessibility services to detect the current active app, so it can show the overlay with the apps chosen by you in the configuration.'

title: Learn Spanish Phrasebook Pro
description:
Learn Spanish is an easy to use mobile Spanish Phrasebook that will give visitors to Spain and those who are interested in learning Spanish a good start in the language. Learn Spanish is recorded using native speaker and we have tried our best to be authentic in the pronunciation whilst ensuring it is easy to understand. Recommended app for tourists and business people visiting Spain.
Features
* Carefully translated list of essential phrases
* High quality audio pronunciation by native speaker
* Play all phrases automatically in each category
* 1,000+ phrases in 18 categories
* Ability to adjust font size
* No internet connection required
* Highlight important words with tips
* Store frequently used phrases in favourites
* Search by keywords
* No adverts or annoying popups
If you like this app and find it useful please take a few seconds to give us a rating in the Android market. For comments and suggestions please send an email to apps@codegent.com. All your feedback and comments are appreciated.

title: Camping Checklist
description:
Now with Cloud Sync & Cloud Share !  Easily backup and sync across devices via the cloud. Share your lists with friends/family and plan your trip together.
Planning a camping trip ? Pre-loaded with more than 225 camping trip related items, this checklist app is all you need to ensure you don't forget anything for your trip. Save hours of typing or creating lists of things to do before your camping trip. Avoid expensive mistakes and be stress free.
PLEASE NOTE: All the features listed in the description are INCLUDED with the purchase.  The in-app purchase option is used only if you want to purchase additional templates (in addition to camping list).  We back our app with 100% refund ANYTIME beyond the refund window. If you are not satisfied for any reason, just send us an email.
New Features! - Cloud Sync & Cloud Share. Tablet support. Quick navigation - just swipe right to reveal the left pane. "Quick add" features. You can add notes, quantity and an additional measurement. Auto sort ability. Checkout more features below.
With options to add/edit/delete/copy/move/rearrange/auto sort and duplicate you can quickly customize the list anyway you want. With support for multiple lists - feel free to create lists for various types of camping trips - short trips / long trips etc.
The app requires internet permission so that you can avail the cloud sync features. If you never register for cloud sync, internet is NOT needed.
Features include:
- Cloud Sync. Easily backup and sync across devices via the cloud.
- Cloud share. Share your lists with friends/family and plan together.
- Tablet support.
- Quick navigation. For small screen devices, just swipe right to reveal the left pane.
- Create new lists from factory templates in minutes.
- Add/Edit or delete lists/items/categories.
- Quickly add item or category from the same screen with the "Quick Add" feature.
- Add Notes, Quantity and an additional measurement (weight/volume/temperature etc) for each item.
- Hide/Unhide checked items, move checked to bottom/top.
- Ability to delete all checked items.
- "Add After This" or "Add Before This" option to insert items wherever you want and quickly.
- Password protect from prying eyes.
- Option to check all/uncheck all so you can reuse the list again.
- Copy or Move between lists, categories and items. Quickly creates your own personal list in matter of minutes.
- Auto Sort either in ascending or descending order.
- Rearrange items/categories/lists using drag/drop.
- Indicates the total number of items and the number of items that need to be completed.
- Color coded (green, yellow and red) for a visually appealing presentation
- Export/Backup all lists to external storage and import them back when needed.
- Edit your list on your computer and import it back.
- Easily email with your friends / family using any sharing client you have on your device.
- Send and share via Bluetooth to any bluetooth enabled device
- Easily send to your printer (via email - Needs email to print support on your printer)

title: British Museum Full Edition
description:
Ready to experience the British Museum? This app will help you discover this world class museum in a fun and easy way, and virtually enjoy the outstanding collection. Unlike the audio guide that needs to be returned, this app will remain in your pocket when you get home, so you can continue to enjoy the British Museum anytime, anywhere. The British Museum is home to the Rosetta stone. But did you know that it is also home to hundreds of other world famous objects?
Included in this App:
- What you must see at the British Museum and where
- A fully interactive map of all the floors
- A virtual walk of the top galleries
- High-resolution images of of the objects.
- Detailed history of the key artifacts
- Information on current events and activities
- Fantastic Walking Tours:
# Top 20
# Top 125
# Greek Mythology Tour
# Mummies Tour
.. many more fascinating tours await you inside the App!  Download now to discover the British Museum without its walls.

title: Thyssen-Bornemisza Museum
description:
The Thyssen-Bornemisza Museum MUSMon.com audioguide explains in a clear, relaxed and accurate way one of the best art galleries in the world. It comfortably guides you, at your own pace, using interactive maps and pictures. It tells you everything you need to know through a 85-minute professional recording, making your visit more entertaining and memorable.
How has womenâ€™s fashion evolved throughout the history of art? What does Henry VIII of Englandâ€™s enigmatic look hide? Who was Toulouse-Lautrec? We give you the answers to these and many other questions.
We will reveal to you the secrets of great masters and works, such as Van Eyck, Goya, Van Gogh or Picasso. We will explain to you the main artistic and historical elements and tell you anecdotes and curiosities about a representative selection of works and authors present in the Madrid museum.
We will guide you on your journey through the history of painting, from the medieval period to the twentieth century art.
The app allows you to:
â€¢Listen to entertaining, quality narrations developed by professionals.
â€¢Quickly and easily find the work you want to listen to through its location on the map, a detailed picture gallery, or a search by author or title.
â€¢Choose between the suggested itineraries or simply guide yourself following your own tastes and time schedule.
â€¢Orientate yourself at any time thanks to the interactive maps.
â€¢Access all the useful information about the museum: opening hours, accessibility, website, etc.
â€¢Read the explanations in text format.
â€¢Forget about queues at the withdrawal and deposits desks. Enjoy this and future visits with the convenience of having everything on your mobile phone.
â€¢Get an excellent view of the evolution of art based on significant masterpieces.

title: German Offline Translator
description:
- Quick and high-quality translation without the internet;
- New â€œDialogâ€ mode for easy communication;
- Instant translation in any app;
- Translation of a text directly from the camera or from photos, which are stored in the Gallery. Works offline!
- Voice translator, dictionary and phrasebook (internet connection is required on certain devices for voice input and output);
- Modern intuitive and responsive interface;
- From German into English, Russian, Spanish, Portuguese, French and vice versa;
- From English into Spanish, Portuguese, French, Russian and vice versa.
100% OFFLINE German translator, phrasebook, and dictionaryâ€”right at your fingertips! This translator is ideal for business, travel and education. The English<->German language package is already included in the app; other languages are available through in-app purchases.
â–º High-quality Translation without the Internet
100% offline translator (an Internet connection is required for the translation of web pages only). Download the app into your device and donâ€™t worry about finding a Wi-Fi hotspot or high roaming charges. Advanced PROMT technology provides excellent translation, even in offline mode. For the most popular topics, including studies, correspondence, social networking, and travel, readymade settings are already included in the interface. Choose the appropriate topic in the app and get the exact translation of words, phrases, whole sentences, websites and SMS texts!
â–º Translation in â€œDialogâ€ mode (New!)
Speech translation in dialog mode will allow you to communicate comfortably anytime and anywhere. Choose the languages for communication, speak your own language and get the translation of your interlocutorâ€™s speech.
â–º Offline Photo Translation
The translation of a text directly from the camera or from photos, which are stored in the Gallery. Just select a text fragment or a word on the image.
â–ºFast One-Tap Translation
You only need to select and copy a word or a text in any app on your device. The translation will appear instantly in the notification area.
â–º Modern Travel Phrasebooks
Download phrasebooks, with ready-made sentences for just about any situation.
â–º Advanced Dictionaries
View dictionary results for single words! You can get translation from different dictionaries, as well as information about parts of speech and transcription. Listen to how words and their translations are pronounced by native speakers.
Easy-to-use links to open additional dictionary content (grammar, translation examples and phrases) in your browser.
â–º Voice Translator
Simply speak a word or phrase and listen to its translation!  Highly recommended while traveling and language learning.
â–º Translation History
View and select the 1000 previously translated words and phrases. Save your translations as Favorites and you will keep them even if you clear the History.
â–º Moderate Size
This app takes up only a little bit of a mobile deviceâ€™s memory: from 30 to 250 MB for one language pair (depending on language and installed components). Text translator should be installed; dictionary and phrasebook can be downloaded separately for free.
You can use an external storage for offline content (SD card).
Love our German Offline Translator? Please rate us on Google Play. Weâ€™re always trying to improve our app. If you have any questions or suggestions, please share them with us support@promt.com!

title: Greater London A-Z 2016
description:
KEY FEATURES
â— Offline street level map for the whole of the Greater London area.
â— Colourful clear custom drawn geographically accurate mapping.
â— No internet connection required, no data roaming charges.
â— GPS location and tracking.
â— Ability to add multiple custom locations, routes and areas directly on the map.
â— Streets, Post codes, Places of interest, Museums and Galleries etc built into the application.
â— Search now also uses internet services when available.
OVERVIEW
This clear colourful and high quality map covers the whole of the Greater London area down to street level. The familiar look of this map makes it by far the easiest London map to use. The map is drawn by real cartographers with the detailed care and human touch of emphasis that A-Z are famous for.
The map covers 3743 sq km (1445 sq miles) of London down to street level, the same area as the printed version of the Master Atlas of Greater London and extends beyond the Greater London and M25 area to Hemel Hempstead, St Albans, Potters Bar, Waltham Cross, Epping, Brentwood, Thurrock, Stanford-le-Hope, Gravesend, Wrotham, Sevenoaks, Westerham, Oxted, Redhill, Reigate, Leatherhead, Great Bookham, Woking, Egham, Windsor, Slough, Chalfont Street Peter, Chorleywood and Bovingdon.
The map index contains over 300,000 entries with nearly 100,000 streets, over 200,000 postcodes, plus thousands of places of interest, hospitals and rail stations. All can be located on this high quality map within a few seconds using the search feature or by browsing the index. The search now reaches out to the internet for additional selections when an internet connection is available.
The map installs completely on the device so that it is available instantly anywhere and with no internet connection..
ANNOTATING THE MAP
You can now add places of interest, routes and areas to the map. This is a very simple yet powerful feature that allows the user to quickly and easily customise their map. This is also a great benefit to anyone planning routes as it instantly displays the distance for the complete route. These annotations can be stored and retrieved instantly on the device.
GPS
You can use your deviceâ€™s inbuilt location services to show your current location on the map or follow your movements as you travel.
Add this map to one of our â€œZutiâ€ route planner maps and you are well equipped to travel anywhere in the Greater London area.
